HEADWORD: Infangthef
<hw>In*fang"thef</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>in-fangen-⟦thorn⟧e⟦oacute⟧f</ets>; <ets>in</ets> in, into +
<ets>fangen</ets> taken (p. p. of <ets>f⟦omac⟧n</ets> to take) +
<ets>⟦thorn⟧e⟦oacute⟧f</ets> thief.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld>
<def>The privilege granted to lords of certain manors to judge thieves
taken within the seigniory of such lords.</def>
<rj><au>Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

